        {
          "username": "Deborah J Thompson-Grinnard",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "117678236696994906573",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 3,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJU6jk1fCzWpVUocLc0EJ0CqTp6uRak5QvPpxmebV1wBTJymg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "My son Noah needed to get an emergency ACL and meniscus repair surgery. He was misdiagnosed by his previous Orthopedic doctor. Dr. Green, I used to get a second opinion because Noah\u2019s knee was only getting progressively worse. I believe from my first meeting with Dr. Green and after reading his review's I knew that I wanted him to perform the surgery. I also spoke to Dr. Cordasco via a phone conference. He was also kind and knowledgeable about what my son needed to recover. This is the only hospital that I will go to get an Orthopedic surgery. Dr. Green and Dr. Cordasco are experts at what they do. Lori, Dr. Cordasco\u2019s PA is thoughtful and kind and was very diligent in ensuring that Noah received the best Physical Therapy. The Both nurses Erica at Lexington Avenue office and the discharge nurse Jennifer at post surgery were very kind, caring and thoughtful. They all came to discuss the procedure with you before and after the surgery. I love the fact that they will continue to monitor Noah\u2019s progress throughout his stages of recovery and even after that. Noah lost his dad 6 months prior to the surgery. He was grieving and feeling hopeless because of his injuries and not being able to play soccer the sport that he loved. I just want to thank Dr. Green, Dr. Cordasco and Staff for the kindness that you showed Noah. What a great organization. You put the \u201cH\u201c back in the word humanity.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT205RVdtcDJVRzVKTFdkUlNXc3hhREEwVHpJNWVGRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xe664ef702671d9b!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm9EWmp2UG5JLWdRSWsxaDA0TzI5eFE%7C%7C?hl=en",
